The paper discusses the evaluation of machine learning-based lithography hotspot detection, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of layout generation tool and the focus on pattern recognition also suggest computer vision (cs.CV) as a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the integration of learning engines in DFM flows, which relates to the sub-categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and control systems (cs.SY).
